reviewText: Well done if under funded. It was good for a one timer.

In THE AWAKENED, a farmer inadvertently unleashes an extra terrestrial nightmare when he pulls out a dead tree on his property. Unbeknownst to him, an alien craft crashed and was buried there 200 years ago. Now, two murderous creatures have been released, and they're extremely hungry! A small band of humans are trapped in the farmhouse, unable to communicate w/ the outside world. Can they survive long enough to defeat these horrors from space? For such a low budget film, THE AWAKENED is excellent. Apart from a few cheeezy moments, and some clunky CGI, it's a well-made sci-fi / horror movie. Robert Picardo (TV's STAR TREK VOYAGER) co-stars as a nefarious government drone...
I liked the movie and thought that the plot was solid but I thought the alien creatures was a little goofy for my taste.

I love me a good monster or creature movie, and this one delivered for me. Its nothing amazing, or groundbreaking, but its a good little alien creature movie with good creature suits and decent acting, give it a watch!!!!
